#: chaotic_pfc.comms.transmitter.transmit:3 of
msgid ""
"Message samples ``m[n]``, shape ``(N,)``. Typically produced by "
":func:`chaotic_pfc.signals.binary_message`."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.transmitter.transmit:5 of
msgid ""
"Modulation depth. Small values (≪ 1) keep the Hénon dynamics near their "
"autonomous regime, which is important for reliable chaos synchronisation "
"at the receiver. The default ``0.01`` matches the convention used "
"throughout the project."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.transmitter.transmit:9
#: chaotic_pfc.comms.transmitter.transmit:10 of
msgid "Hénon parameters. The canonical chaotic regime is ``(1.4, 0.3)``."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.comms.transmitter.transmit:11
#: chaotic_pfc.comms.transmitter.transmit:12 of
msgid "Initial conditions of the transmitter's internal state."
msgstr ""

